<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1485">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/257.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Nicaraguan Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 12]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 7th instant, in which you inform me that a
                            contract [etc.]</p>
                        <p>In reply, I have the honor to inform you that the name of Clifford D.
                            Ham, at present Surveyor of the Port of Manila, has been placed in
                            nomination by Messrs. Brown Brothers and Company and J. and W. Seligman
                            and Company to fill the post of Collector-General of Customs of
                            Nicaragua, and that I have this day approved his nomination as a
                            suitable and competent person to fill that position.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>